Description:
Brilliant Townhouse With Views And Double-Glazing
Big, bright and boutique, this unique in design two bedroom, two bathroom owner-occupied townhouse benefits from a brilliant northerly orientation and boasts vast double-glazed aspects capturing leafy parkland views.
Secured by intercom and foyer entry, the home's quality, finishes and generous size is immediately evident from the moment you arrive.
Awash with natural light are large open plan living, meals spaces featuring high ceilings, solid hardwood floors and glass sliders opening wide onto a sun-filled balcony where you can take in views of nearby Merri Creek trails and sports precincts.
Adding further appeal for discerning buyers is a well appointed kitchen displaying a host of stainless steel Fisher& Paykel appliances, Bosch dishwasher, abundant storage solutions and stone counter tops, including breakfast bar.
Private accommodation comprises two oversized bedrooms with high ceilings, generous built-in-robes and plush carpet.
Both enjoy modern ensuites and balcony access.
Complemented by three split-system units, guest powder room, European laundry, under stair storage, linen cupboard and secure basement car space and storage cage on title.
Moments from central Coburg shops, markets, cafes, leisure centres, trains and schools, with easy CBD and airport access and only metres from Nicholson Street trams, while Bell Street buses pass the door.
Insights: 7/7-9 Bell Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 73 other 2 bedroom unit in Coburg have recently been sold.

A real find indeed.

Description:
Location, Lifestyle and Spacious Living in Coburg!
Be the proud owner of this spacious two bedroom apartment located in the heart of Coburg along the banks of Merri Creek.
A spacious open living layout with a well-appointed stylish kitchen and living area that extends to a superb courtyard for outdoor entertaining. The well-appointed master bedroom with ensuite is complemented by a second bedroom with study nook and additional bathroom, while other modern amenities include a separate spacious laundry, ample internal storage and split system with heating and cooling options.
The secure carpark allocated on the ground floor with easy access to the apartment via the courtyard, makes bringing in the shopping a breeze and highly versatile for young families and elderly wanting to avoid the stairs and lifts.
Located in the well-known 'Merriview Place' apartments which comes with access to a 25m outdoor pool, barbeques facilities and change rooms it presents the ultimate in summer entertainment.
Situated just moments to recreational facilities, it encourages a healthy outdoor lifestyle.
It's also close to public transport, Coburg Village, Local schools and Sydney Road cafes making it the ideal apartment for city edge living.

Description:
Your Piece of Pentridge Village History!
Families will love this fabulous home with modern interiors, spacious layout and featuring a crisp contemporary palette. Oversized rooms and zoned spaces offers the ideal setting for shared living.
The ground floor features open plan living and dining, which interact directly with the kitchen and the social, private courtyard. The home chef will be in their element with an abundance of preparation and storage space, black granite benchtops, tiled splashback, gas cooktop, dishwasher, and double sink. Also on the ground floor, a fully facilitated laundry with toilet and storage room.
The bedrooms are zoned upstairs, all sharing a central bathroom with separate toilet. The Master bedroom offers a walk-in robe and adjoining access to the bathroom, and the other two bedrooms have built-in robes. A minor renovation could easily see the Master bedroom enjoying a personal ensuite in addition to the central bathroom – see prospective floorplan (or ask for further details). Further features of the property include double garaging, ducted heating, and external landscaping.
As part of the famed Pentridge Village Development, residents will love being a part of this developing community. Already home to The Glass Den – a beautiful restaurant – and frequent art/food/drink events held in B Division, the site is set to welcome much more in the near future, including cinemas, a supermarket, high-end hotel, and much more. Just 9km north of Melbourne CBD, commuters will love the short ride to work in the morning, with the nearby #19 tram running frequently to and from the city and Coburg Station is only minutes away. Enjoy walks along the Merri Creek trail on weekends, a short stroll to the Saturday Farmers' Market or play tennis at the East Coburg Tennis Club.

Description:
Good Times Start Here
Exuding individual appeal, this four/five bedroom, two bathroom home is a haven in a handy locale ready to embrace a new family. A rarely seen Queensland style home, later extended, it offers a living/dining, family/meals, kitchen, balcony with views of the Dandenongs, northerly rear garden and covered entertaining area/off street parking accessing a rear ROW. Most of the four double bedrooms include BIRs, one leads to a secret room and the study is easily large enough for a comfortable fifth bedroom. Further highlights include a modern ground floor bathroom, inverter heating/cooling, Electrolux and Miele appliances, roof storage, high ceilings, period details and wraparound balcony. Parks, trains, trams, Upfield Bike Path and Sydney Road shops are a stroll and schools nearby.

Description:
Commanding Presence
Showcasing luxurious living and entertaining with a raft of great features, this spacious four bedroom residence is conveniently located at the end of a cul-de-sac filled with handsome family homes. Inspiring spaces include a lounge with bay window, paved entertainer's haven and vast open family/dining/kitchen resplendent with expansive stone countertops. Stainless steel appliances from brands including Blanco and Bosch meet with white tiled splashbacks, deep drawers and cupboards in creating an ideal environment for culinary pursuits. Three large bedrooms with robes include a main bedroom with a walk-in robe and marble accented ensuite, while the study is an excellent size and could easily be used as a comfortable bedroom. The gleaming family bathroom hosts a spa and separate shower and there's a powder room on each of the two storeys. This impeccably presented home impresses on all fronts: great storage, high ceilings, polished floorboards, an elegant staircase, ducted heating, central cooling, ducted vacuum, video intercom, tasteful landscaping and a remote double garage with direct entry also feature. Stroll to transport, parks, schools, Lake Reserve, Coburg Farmers' Market, sporting facilities, The Boot Factory cafe and Sydney Road.

Description:
UNDER OFFER
In a blissfully quiet cul-de-sac opposite Merri Creek parkland and endless trails, this two-storey home with its own street frontage is sure to make an impression thanks to its generous floorplan, quality inclusions and abundance of natural light throughout. Absolutely immaculate interior comprises three spacious bedrooms (master with WIR and ensuite), main central bathroom and guest powder room (third WC). Add to this an expansive open-plan living/dining area enhanced by a sleek stone-top kitchen with tiled splashbacks, stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Other highlights of the home include split-system heating and cooling (living area and all bedrooms), new carpets, European laundry, large linen cupboard and additional under-stair storage space. Step outside to a wonderfully private rear courtyard and remote-control double garage (via ROW) complete with attic ladder to vast storage area above. Conveniently positioned, it's also walking distance to Coburg High School, De Chene Reserve and Coburg Lake, as well as easy access to Coburg Station and renowned shopping centre, Sydney Road trams, cafes and restaurants.
Insights: 9/1 Manna Gum Court, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Brand-New Designer Living - Last one Available
With its intelligent architecture, floorplan flexibility and luxurious appointments throughout, this fully-optioned home delivers an exclusive environment of cutting-edge style and enviable inner-urban convenience. With its own street frontage and no shared land, the home's meticulously-detailed interior boasts four bedrooms (all with designer mirrored robes) and dedicated study with built-in workstation, deluxe ensuite, main bathroom and two powder rooms (one on each level) - all with floor-to-ceiling tiles. Add to this an expansive open-plan living/dining area complemented by a gourmet kitchen with stone benchtops and splashbacks, ample cupboard space, Smeg 900mm cooking appliances, integrated microwave oven and dishwasher. Other premium features include heating and cooling throughout, comprehensive security system (alarm, video intercom and CCTV), ducted vacuum, American Oak solid timber floors and soft-close cabinetry, full-size laundry and under-stair storeroom. Double-glazed stacker doors (from the living area) reveal a sunny rear courtyard complete with Blackbutt entertaining deck, synthetic turf and permitter gardens, plus the added advantage of an internally-accessed garage (remote-controlled) and additional driveway parking space. Well south of Bell Street, the best of Coburg is at your fingertips including trains, trams and buses, renowned shops and major supermarkets, cafes and restaurants, as well as easy access to local parks and schools.
Insights: 1 Mayfield Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 49 other 4 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
A villa that's set to surprise
Make the most of a vibrant urban lifestyle with this impressive three bedroom villa unit, whose bright free flowing interiors and embracing courtyard garden are set to surprise. In a boutique block of three, this completely private property features sunlit living and dining separated by stacker doors and serviced by a quality appointed easy care kitchen. The wraparound courtyard a pleasant surprise with an alfresco area and garden beds creating a relaxed outdoor space. Three bedrooms with built-in robes share a pristine bathroom, that together with ducted heating, separate laundry, single garage and car space, make it an ideal first home, downsizer or savvy investment. In a vibrant location it boasts Sydney Road shopping and trams, Coburg Station and Merri Creek trails walking distance.

Description:
Superb Living, Distinctively Donne
This distinctive two bedroom Californian Bungalow is an absolute delight, offering charismatic entry to one of Coburg's premier pockets. Superbly updated this beautiful home celebrates its period pedigree showcasing original leadlight windows, Baltic Pine floors, ornate ceilings and panelled walls of the era, while presenting a free-flowing floorplan that shines a light on indoor-outdoor entertaining and modern lifestyle needs.
A spacious living domain extends gracefully off a wide hallway with gleaming double leadlight doors, presenting a sunlit lounge with gas-log fireplace and dining centred around a quality appointed stone topped island kitchen. French doors open to an entertainer's deck and landscaped gardens resplendent with fruit trees that incorporates a rustic bar with an enclosed wood fireplace for effortless year-round entertaining.
Private bedrooms, master with double doors to a romantic verandah, enjoy built-in robes and spacious family bathroom with traditional slipper tub, while a sunlit study, ducted heating, split system cooling, separate laundry, storage shed and side drive offering ample off street parking assure complete comfort. In a true lifestyle local surrounded by parks, schools including St Fideles Primary School, Melville Road trams, the specialty shopping, cafes and transport of Sydney Road and easy CityLink access, inspection will impress.
Insights: 52 Donne Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 58 other 2 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Stylish Living In Historical Pentridge Estate
This trendy warehouse conversion perfectly blend contemporary finishes with the historical features of the Woollen Mills development of Pentridge Estate. Including exposed red brick walls, original wooden beams and cast iron columns, the bright open plan living space contains an ultramodern kitchen, showcasing Caesarstone benches, 2-pack cabinetry and under stair storage, whilst the dining and lounge lead to a private courtyard, with built in seating, Merbau decking and heritage bluestone wall. Upstairs, two light filled and generous bedrooms, each with built in robes and soaring pitched roof, share a chic central bathroom with oversized shower. With split system air conditioning throughout, video intercom, video security, secure single car space including extra storage and visitors parking, this fabulous townhouse is a stone's throw from the Merri Creek trail and Sydney Road shopping precinct, with city bound tram and Batman train station nearby.
Insights: 8/1 Industry Lane, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 58 other 2 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
AUCTION - This Saturday 8th of September at 12pm
This beautiful double fronted north facing period home is sure to entice, with its carefully curated renovation and generous block of land totalling approximately 507 m2.
The home's interior warmly presents a spacious entry hall via double doors, high ceilings, a flexible floor plan comprising of three large bedrooms (including BIRs), contemporary central bathroom with designer European fittings from Rogerseller, living, dining and kitchen featuring a freestanding 900mm Ariston stainless steel cooker.
Other features include zoned gas ducted heating, evaporative cooling, and polished floorboards.
The expansive private backyard has an additional 4th bedroom/studio, second WC, laundry/store and plenty of space to entertain or extend (STCA), with convenient rear access via a double carport with automatic door.
Located opposite McDonald Reserve, the convenient location offers easy access to Coburg and Bell stations, Nicholson Street and Sydney Road trams, buses, local schools and shops. It's only a short stroll to the Merri Creek trail, cafes and restaurants including Ruby's, Glass Den and Cornerstone Pizzeria.
Picture perfect! The hard work has been done, nothing more to do than move in and enjoy the beauty and convenient location.

Immediate Family Style with Elevated Potential!

Description:
Californian Class with Extended Perfection

Surprisingly spacious interior showcases four bedrooms (large master with fully-fitted robes and deluxe ensuite), main bathroom and separate powder room. Dual living zones include a separate lounge and spacious open-plan living/dining area enhanced by a French Provincial-inspired chef's kitchen with stone benches, timber-top island/breakfast bar, Falcon oven, dual Fisher & Paykel dish drawers, pressed-metal splashbacks and walk-in pantry. Other highlights of the home include heating and cooling throughout, C-bus automated lighting, blinds, alarm, access control, CCTV, double-glazed windows, modern laundry and ample storage cupboards, plus undercover entertaining deck complete with kitchen servery, sizeable backyard with workshop/storeroom and secure off-street parking option via remote-controlled rollerdoor to ROW. Description:
Edwardian Gem with Extra-Wide Appeal
On a substantial block of land complete with its own side driveway, this freestanding period home presents an impressive inner-urban lifestyle opportunity with its immediate comfort, expansion potential (STCA) and close proximity to everything Coburg has to enjoy. Immaculately-maintained interior comprises two genuinely large bedrooms, neat bathroom and separate WC, wide lounge flowing through to the dining area and adjoining kitchen. Additional features of the home include gas heating and cooling, high ceilings and solid timber floors, internal laundry facilities, plus a sizable backyard with undercover patio, garage (via driveway) and additional off-street parking option via rear ROW. A prime location walking distance to Sydney Road trams and cafes, it's also close to Moreland Station, local schools , popular restaurants and cosmopolitan shopping precinct. Position, promise and potential!

Description:
Merriview Place – The ultimate urban resort lifestyle
This park side single bedroom ‘Merriview Place’ 62 sqm apartment welcomes contemporary style, space and tranquillity.
Whether you are a first home buyer or the savvy investor, this bright and spacious apartment caters open living, stylish well-appointed central kitchen, and opens out to the large private terrace overlooking the beautiful natural surrounding parklands.
With unique apartment features including :
• Spacious open plan living
• Generous double sized bedroom with BIRs
• Modern en-suite with oversized shower
• Stylish kitchen with stainless steel appliances and electric cooktop
• Large balcony with views of Merri Creek Reserve
• Separate guest powder room (second toilet)
• Fully equipped separate laundry
• Split system air conditioning/heating
• Secure undercover parking with personal storage facilities
• Secure access via video intercom
The Merriview Apartment complex is located just moments to recreational facilities, encouraging a healthy outdoor lifestyle. With close proximity to public transport, Coburg Village and Sydney Road cafes. The complex within the notorious Pentridge Village Estate provides its residents with ‘Maximum Security’ safety, and a community lifestyle for all to enjoy.
The Merriview community features include :
• Gated community with secure access via video intercom
• CCTV foyer surveillance
• Fully maintained swimming pool with access to change room facilities
• Communal BBQ and courtyard ideal for large summer gatherings
Providing an excellent investment opportunity, the property is currently leased returning $1,478 per calendar month.
Any new investor or downsizer will certainly appreciate the immaculate presentation and low maintenance surrounds providing the perfect urban resort lifestyle.

Description:
A diamond in the rough
Classically original in appearance and loaded with potential, the charm of this Edwardian beauty is significant for all sorts of reasons! This comfortable residence with a strikingly wide hallway offers three generous sized bedrooms, a central bathroom with bathtub and a stunning separate lounge with original fireplace feature. To the rear a fantastic older style kitchen adjoining the meals with a door opening out to the sun-filled rear yard with a fantastic garage great for storage (laneway access), an additional storage shed and an outdoor WC.
Added highlights to this stunning residence include wall mounted heating and cooling units, ornate ceiling cornices and rosettes, original open fire places throughout, high ceilings, polished timber floorboards, and original lead light windows and doors. The possibilities to transform this residence into your dream home are endless- retain or renovate the already comfortable floor plan or utilise the substantial roof cavity and rear yard to develop up and out STCA.
Minutes away from trains, trams and buses, enjoy this fabulous Coburg home set in a quiet cul-de-sac, five minutes from Sydney Road shops, surrounding schools and parklands.

Description:
Architect Designed Renovation With Impressive Indoor/Outdoor Space
In a boutique block of five, this distinctive front townhouse is a must-see for professionals and investors alike with its free-flowing design, premium features throughout and oversized courtyard surprise. Bathed in northerly light, the home's inviting interior boasts two large bedrooms (both with full-width robes), deluxe central bathroom and separate WC. Add to this an expansive open living area, dining room and adjoining kitchen complete with tiled splashbacks and Bosch cooking appliances. Other highlights include gas heating, split-system air conditioning (living area and both bedrooms), high vaulted ceilings, motorised security shutters, new carpets and floors, full-size laundry, plus undercover parking space along with a wonderfully large and sunny courtyard with its own second entrance. Walking distance to Moreland Station, Sydney Road trams and cafes, it's also close to Coburg's renowned shopping precinct, popular schools and local parks, as well as easy access to Citylink.
